value.0: A carefully constructed marker denoting a point of interest.
This well made small shield is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments, it appears as ready for battle as ever. This particular shield is of Calishite make.
When used properly, a small shield can grant lightweight protection with very little encumbrance to the wielder.

When used properly, a small shield can grant lightweight protection with very little encumbrance to the wielder.
This enchanted garment provided the wearer the ability to resist the elements once per day- the spell itself lasting 24 hours.
This "cestys" or spiked knuckle is rather common in Calimport, where it is often used to take advantage of unsuspecting folk.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
These arrows boast an amount of flamable material by the arrowhead.
These finely crafted bolts bear a firey enchantment that makes them very desirable in combat.
This spear or "Enaza" is of Calishite make. It is exceptional to say the least.
Another of history's most basic weapons, the spear is nevertheless a formidable weapon.  Little more than a simple shaft topped with a sharpened head, the spear is the staple of many a militia.
This well made falchion was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.

The falchion is a brutal, hacking weapon.  Not suble, and not good for defense.  It is however a fairly simple and inexpensive weapon to make because its broad, heavy blade can be forged thickly of cheap metal by inexperienced smiths.
The jambiya is a hooked dagger worn by almost all Calishite men. Calishites seem to favor curved blades in general.
The jikholnar was a handaxe favored by Calishites... it followed in their proclivity toward curved weapons.
The kholnar was a devastating axe, the form and design which was perfected over the course of generations in Calimshan.
The Sikaena was a wicked, cruel weapon meant for killing people who weren't wearing armor. It was a thing from the days when assassinations were much more common in Calimshan.
This finely crafted shortbow was made using secrets shared by the elves of the Wealdath.
This finely crafted bow was made with secrets shared by the elves of the Wealdath.

The caviler is a shorter form of the arquebus that arrived along with many other innovations with smoke powder weaponry after the Time of Troubles. This particular weapon has a remarkable level of craftsmanship.
The jezail is a form of long gun that followed innovations with smoke powder weaponry after the Time of Troubles. This particular model is very popular in Calimshan and Amn.
This is an amount of lead bullets, intended for use in a smoke powder weapon.
This is an amount of improved lead rounds, intended for use in a smoke powder weapon.
This is an amount of arcane bullets, intended for use in a smoke powder weapon.
These are lead rounds created with some amount of fire magic within them. They are intended for use in a smoke powder weapon.
This strange fluid seems to have separated oils in it, but when applied to diseased flesh its effects are almost instantaneously felt.
This strong smelling potion offers substantial healing from physical harm.
A note on this incendiary device warns to handle it with care.
This tent is of some quality make. It seems as though it will help when the temperature drops, remain standing when strong winds blow, and keep you dry during heavy rainstorms.
